comment: None of the managers/employees care what your gender identity is. You probably don't have to be a paying customer as no one in the kitchen can see when people walk in they just get a bell for when the door opens, however ordering something small never hurts (a small personal pan pizza is 3.99 if you don't want to have to spend a lot). They installed a trashcan inside of the men's restroom stall for men who still have that time of the month.

name: Union Station
directions:
There are two in Union. One is near the McDonalds in the GO Station area. Where the gendered washrooms split into two it’s in the centre. Can’t miss it. 

The second one is towards the TTC subway system. It’s around the corner from Wurst (across the hall from the security window) and there are signs. The first bathroom you see is an accessible one. There’s a colour indicator on the button beside the door that tells you if it’s locked. Red = locked.
comment: The first restroom near the McDonalds is usually closed or dirty. Go to the second one when possible.
